<subSubSection pageId="44" pageNumber="195" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,426,775]" pageId="44" pageNumber="195">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,260,426,451]" pageId="44" pageNumber="195">Remarks</emphasis>
. From study of the description and 
<typeStatus box="[681,729,427,451]" pageId="44" pageNumber="195">type</typeStatus>
specimens (at 
<collectionCode box="[906,994,427,450]" pageId="44" pageNumber="195">BMNH</collectionCode>
; 
<figureCitation box="[1008,1175,426,451]" captionStart="FIGURES 148 – 155" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1912,1935]" captionTargetBox="[232,1351,202,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[232,1354,193,1892]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 148 – 155. Mesomphalia species: 148 – 151, Mesomphalia nudoplagiata Spaeth, 1901: 148, male, dorsal view; 149, female, dorsal view; 150, lateral view; 151, syntype, dorsal view; 152 – 153, Cyrtonota pyramidata (Boheman, 1850): 152, dorsal view; 153, lateral view; 154 – 155, Stolas scrobiculata (Boheman, 1850): 154, dorsal view; 155, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/249808/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="195">
Figs. 
<number box="[1073,1175,426,451]" pageId="44" pageNumber="195" value="152.5" valueMax="153.0" valueMin="152.0">152–153</number>
</figureCitation>
), this species does not belong in 
<taxonomicName box="[263,415,462,487]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[263,415,462,487]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="195">Mesomphalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,426,775]" pageId="44" pageNumber="195">
<taxonomicName box="[199,490,498,523]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyramidata">
<emphasis box="[199,490,498,523]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="195">Mesomphalia pyramidata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares the following characters with 
<taxonomicName box="[925,1039,499,522]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cyrtonota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[925,1039,499,522]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="195">Cyrtonota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: five basal antennal segments and pronotum glabrous, prosternal collar without lateral projections at apical margin or median transverse sulcus. These features are lacking in 
<taxonomicName box="[414,567,570,595]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[414,567,570,595]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="195">Mesomphalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We therefore place this species in 
<taxonomicName box="[977,1090,571,594]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cyrtonota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[977,1090,571,594]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="195">Cyrtonota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as 
<taxonomicName box="[1139,1303,570,595]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyramidata">
<emphasis box="[1139,1303,570,595]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="195">C. pyramidata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Boheman, 
<number box="[151,223,606,631]" pageId="44" pageNumber="195" value="12850.0">12850</number>
) 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[237,358,606,631]" pageId="44" pageNumber="195">comb. nov</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[371,621,606,631]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cyrtonota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyramidata">
<emphasis box="[371,621,606,631]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="195">Cyrtonota pyramidata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can also be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[975,1128,606,631]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="195" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[975,1128,606,631]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="195">Mesomphalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by: color pattern of black with red spots and strongly punctate elytra; frontoclypeus not swollen; absence of tufts of setae on pronotum and elytra.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,426,775]" box="[199,1038,714,739]" pageId="44" pageNumber="195">
